<DocsLayout title="Changelog — Band Docs">
  <h1>Changelog</h1>
  <p>
    Notable changes and releases for Band. For the complete commit history, see the
    <a href="https://github.com/band-app/band/releases">GitHub releases page</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>v0.1.0 — Initial Release</h2>
  <p>The first public release of Band.</p>

  <h3>Features</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Desktop dashboard</strong> — Native macOS Electron app with project sidebar, workspace list, and status indicators. Signed and notarized via Apple Developer ID.</li>
    <li><strong>Web interface</strong> — Browser-based dashboard with responsive layout for desktop and mobile</li>
    <li><strong>Multi-IDE support</strong> — VS Code, Cursor, Zed, Windsurf, Kiro, all JetBrains IDEs, Xcode, iTerm2, Warp, Ghostty, Chrome, Safari, Firefox</li>
    <li><strong>Multi-agent support</strong> — Claude Code, Cursor CLI, OpenAI Codex (SDK), Codex (CLI), Gemini CLI, and OpenCode via a pluggable adapter pattern</li>
    <li><strong>Git worktree workspaces</strong> — Isolated branch-per-task workflow with automatic worktree management</li>
    <li><strong>Chat panes</strong> — Per-workspace multi-agent chat panes with message streaming, abort, and history paging</li>
    <li><strong>Scheduled cronjobs</strong> — Cron-based automation for recurring agent work, scoped to a project or a specific workspace</li>
    <li><strong>Remote access</strong> — Built-in Cloudflare tunnel with token-based authentication and QR code for mobile</li>
    <li><strong>CLI</strong> — Resource-based command groups (<code>projects</code>, <code>workspaces</code>, <code>chats</code>, <code>terminals</code>, <code>browsers</code>, <code>cronjobs</code>, <code>tunnel</code>, <code>settings</code>) with JSON output mode</li>
    <li><strong>Project configuration</strong> — Per-project <code>.band/config.json</code> with setup/teardown commands and app presets</li>
    <li><strong>Claude Code hooks</strong> — Auto-installed <code>PreToolUse</code>, <code>PermissionRequest</code>, <code>UserPromptSubmit</code>, <code>PostToolUse</code>, and <code>Stop</code> hooks that report agent status back to Band via <code>band notify</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Architecture</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Desktop shell built with Electron + TypeScript</li>
    <li>Dashboard frontend built with React 19, TanStack Router, and Vite</li>
    <li>Web server built with Node.js 22.5+ and tRPC</li>
    <li>CLI built with Rust</li>
    <li>SQLite via Node's built-in <code>node:sqlite</code> module for persistent state</li>
    <li>tRPC over HTTP with Server-Sent Events for chat streaming and WebSocket for terminals and LSP</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
